{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01RpXW83QJq24abqs9Aj7G3q","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent. Now I have all the information. Let me compile a comprehensive report:\n\n---\n\n## Queue/Worker Infrastructure Report\n\nI've completed a thorough analysis of the backend queue/worker infrastructure. Here's the detailed breakdown:\n\n### 1. **Registry Pattern (Handler Registration)**\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/queue/handler-registry.ts`\n\nThe registry uses a simple Map-based pattern with three public functions:\n\n- `registerHandler(eventType: EventType, handler: EventHandler)` — registers a handler function for an event type\n- `getHandler(eventType: string): EventHandler | undefined` — retrieves the handler at dispatch time\n- `clearHandlers()` — test utility to clear all handlers for isolation\n\nKey design:\n- One handler per event type (no pub/sub fan-out in v1)\n- Handlers must be **idempotent** — re-processing is a safe no-op\n- Handler type: `(payload: Record<string, unknown>) => Promise<void>`\n- No context object passed to handlers; all data flows through the payload\n\n### 2. **EventTypes Definition**\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/queue/event-types.ts`\n\nCurrently three event types:\n```typescript\nEventTypes = {\n  REFERRAL_CODE_APPLIED: \"referral.code_applied\",\n  REFERRAL_GAME_SETTLED: \"referral.game_settled\",\n  REFERRAL_CLAIM_REQUESTED: \"referral.claim_requested\",\n}\n```\n\nPattern: const object + derived union type prevents typos at compile time.\n\n### 3. **Emitting Events**\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/queue/emit-event.ts`\n\nSignature:\n```typescript\nasync function emitEvent(\n  tx: SqlOrTransaction,\n  eventType: EventType,\n  payload: Record<string, unknown>,\n  options?: EmitEventOptions,\n): Promise<{ eventId: bigint }>\n```\n\n**Critical**: Events are emitted within an existing database transaction, ensuring **atomic commitment** with the triggering operation. If the transaction rolls back, the event is NOT persisted (verified by tests).\n\n**Options**:\n- `maxAttempts` (default: 3) — max retry attempts before marking event dead\n- `scheduledAt` (default: now) — defer processing until a specific time (enables scheduling)\n\n**Usage Pattern** (from referral claim):\n```typescript\nconst claim = await sql.begin(async (tx) => {\n  // Insert claim row\n  const rows = await (tx as unknown as postgres.Sql)`\n    INSERT INTO referral_claims (...)\n    VALUES (...)\n    RETURNING ...\n  `;\n  \n  // Emit event in same transaction\n  await emitEvent(\n    tx as unknown as postgres.Sql,\n    EventTypes.REFERRAL_CLAIM_REQUESTED,\n    {\n      claimId: row.id,\n      wallet: row.wallet,\n      amountLamports: row.amount_lamports,\n      requestedAt: new Date().toISOString(),\n    },\n  );\n  \n  return row;\n});\n```\n\n### 4. **Worker Processing**\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/queue/worker.ts`\n\nThe worker polls the `event_queue` table and dispatches events. Key behaviors:\n\n**Concurrency Safety**:\n- Uses `FOR UPDATE SKIP LOCKED` to claim batches atomically\n- Multiple workers can safely poll simultaneously (each event processed exactly once)\n\n**Poll Cycle**:\n1. Claim a batch of `pending` events scheduled for now\n2. Move them to `processing` status, record `started_at`\n3. For each event:\n   - Look up the registered handler\n   - Call handler with the payload\n   - On success: mark `completed`, record `completed_at`\n   - On failure: increment `attempts`, apply exponential backoff, reschedule as `pending`\n   - On exhausted retries: mark `dead`, record error message and `completed_at`\n\n**Error Handling**:\n- If no handler is registered: mark event `dead` immediately with alert-level logging (\"MANUAL REVIEW NEEDED\")\n- If handler throws: retry with exponential backoff: attempt 1 → 5s, attempt 2 → 30s, attempt 3+ → 300s\n- Unregistered event types are detected at runtime and logged as dead events\n\n**Status Transitions**:\n```\npending → processing → completed\n       ↓\n       → pending (with scheduled_at + backoff) → processing → completed\n       ↓ (max attempts exhausted)\n       → dead\n```\n\n**Concurrency Model**:\n- `setTimeout(loop, pollIntervalMs)` pattern (same as settlement worker)\n- In-flight poll tracked so `stop()` waits for current batch to finish\n- Default poll interval: 1500ms\n- Default batch size: 10\n\n**Initialization** (from `src/index.ts`):\n```typescript\nconst eventWorker = createEventWorker(sql, {\n  pollIntervalMs: config.eventQueuePollMs,\n});\neventWorker.start();\n```\n\n### 5. **Database Schema**\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/services/backend/migrations/010_event_queue.sql`\n\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE event_queue (\n  id              BIGSERIAL    PRIMARY KEY,\n  event_type      TEXT         NOT NULL,\n  payload         JSONB        NOT NULL,\n  status          TEXT         NOT NULL DEFAULT 'pending',\n  attempts        INTEGER      NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n  max_attempts    INTEGER      NOT NULL DEFAULT 3,\n  scheduled_at    TIMESTAMPTZ  NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),\n  started_at      TIMESTAMPTZ,\n  completed_at    TIMESTAMPTZ,\n  error           TEXT,\n  created_at      TIMESTAMPTZ  NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),\n  \n  CONSTRAINT chk_event_queue_status\n    CHECK (status IN ('pending', 'processing', 'completed', 'failed', 'dead'))\n);\n\n-- Partial index for polling (only pending events)\nCREATE INDEX idx_event_queue_poll\n  ON event_queue (scheduled_at)\n  WHERE status = 'pending';\n\n-- Index for observability\nCREATE INDEX idx_event_queue_status\n  ON event_queue (status, created_at);\n```\n\nPayload is stored as JSONB for flexibility and query-ability.\n\n### 6. **Existing Handlers (None Yet Implemented)**\n\n**Current Status**: No handler implementations exist yet. The infrastructure is ready but all three event types (`REFERRAL_CODE_APPLIED`, `REFERRAL_GAME_SETTLED`, `REFERRAL_CLAIM_REQUESTED`) have no registered handlers.\n\nThis is safe because:\n- Dead events are marked immediately with alert-level logging\n- The event is persisted in the database for manual inspection/replay\n- No silent failures\n\n### 7. **Testing Infrastructure**\n\n**Unit Tests** (`queue.test.ts`):\n- Event insertion with atomic rollback\n- Handler registry get/register\n- Backoff calculation\n\n**Integration Tests** (`queue-integration.test.ts`):\n- Happy path: handler called → event status = completed\n- Failure → retry → dead: attempts incremented, backoff applied\n- Concurrent safety: two workers processing same batch simultaneously, each event exactly once\n\n### 8. **Health/Observability**\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/queue/health.ts`\n\nExports `getQueueDepth()`:\n```typescript\ninterface QueueDepth {\n  pending: number;\n  processing: number;\n  dead: number;\n  completed: number;\n}\n```\n\nQueries the event_queue table grouped by status. Used for monitoring dead events and queue congestion.\n\n---\n\n## Key Patterns Summary\n\n| Aspect | Pattern |\n|--------|---------|\n| **Handler Registration** | Simple `Map<string, handler>` — register once at startup |\n| **Payload Shape** | `Record<string, unknown>` — flexible, schema-less |\n| **Idempotency** | Handlers must be idempotent; no guarantees of single delivery |\n| **Error Handling** | Exponential backoff (5s → 30s → 300s) → dead with error message |\n| **Atomicity** | Events emitted within tx; rolled back if tx fails |\n| **Concurrency** | `FOR UPDATE SKIP LOCKED` on poll; safe for multiple workers |\n| **Scheduling** | `scheduledAt` column enables deferred processing |\n| **Observability** | Dead events logged at WARN level; status/created_at indexed |\n\n---\n\n## File Paths (Absolute)\n\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/queue/event-types.ts` — event type constants\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/queue/handler-registry.ts` — registration/dispatch\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/queue/emit-event.ts` — event producer\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/queue/worker.ts` — polling + dispatch engine\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/queue/health.ts` — queue depth queries\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/queue/index.ts` — public exports\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/migrations/010_event_queue.sql` — schema\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/routes/referral.ts` — example usage (POST /claim)\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/index.ts` — worker initialization"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: adb6bfa73cc7fcf30 (use SendMessage with to: 'adb6bfa73cc7fcf30' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 59086\ntool_uses: 21\nduration_ms: 104503</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"666b10e8-ff74-42a6-8a85-f241f06f2d89","uuid":"df433ef9-5d72-459b-9d12-7ce4ef274010","timestamp":"2026-03-25T12:40:26.106Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Find and read the queue/worker infrastructure in `sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/`. I need to understand:\n1. How event handlers are registered (the registry pattern)\n2. What existing handlers look like (payload shape, error handling, idempotency)\n3. Where EventTypes are defined\n4. How emitEvent works\n5. The worker.ts file that processes events\n\nRead the relevant files fully and report the patterns. Be thorough - check src/queue/, src/worker/, or wherever this infrastructure lives.","agentId":"adb6bfa73cc7fcf30","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent. Now I have all the information. Let me compile a comprehensive report:\n\n---\n\n## Queue/Worker Infrastructure Report\n\nI've completed a thorough analysis of the backend queue/worker infrastructure. Here's the detailed breakdown:\n\n### 1. **Registry Pattern (Handler Registration)**\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/queue/handler-registry.ts`\n\nThe registry uses a simple Map-based pattern with three public functions:\n\n- `registerHandler(eventType: EventType, handler: EventHandler)` — registers a handler function for an event type\n- `getHandler(eventType: string): EventHandler | undefined` — retrieves the handler at dispatch time\n- `clearHandlers()` — test utility to clear all handlers for isolation\n\nKey design:\n- One handler per event type (no pub/sub fan-out in v1)\n- Handlers must be **idempotent** — re-processing is a safe no-op\n- Handler type: `(payload: Record<string, unknown>) => Promise<void>`\n- No context object passed to handlers; all data flows through the payload\n\n### 2. **EventTypes Definition**\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/queue/event-types.ts`\n\nCurrently three event types:\n```typescript\nEventTypes = {\n  REFERRAL_CODE_APPLIED: \"referral.code_applied\",\n  REFERRAL_GAME_SETTLED: \"referral.game_settled\",\n  REFERRAL_CLAIM_REQUESTED: \"referral.claim_requested\",\n}\n```\n\nPattern: const object + derived union type prevents typos at compile time.\n\n### 3. **Emitting Events**\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/queue/emit-event.ts`\n\nSignature:\n```typescript\nasync function emitEvent(\n  tx: SqlOrTransaction,\n  eventType: EventType,\n  payload: Record<string, unknown>,\n  options?: EmitEventOptions,\n): Promise<{ eventId: bigint }>\n```\n\n**Critical**: Events are emitted within an existing database transaction, ensuring **atomic commitment** with the triggering operation. If the transaction rolls back, the event is NOT persisted (verified by tests).\n\n**Options**:\n- `maxAttempts` (default: 3) — max retry attempts before marking event dead\n- `scheduledAt` (default: now) — defer processing until a specific time (enables scheduling)\n\n**Usage Pattern** (from referral claim):\n```typescript\nconst claim = await sql.begin(async (tx) => {\n  // Insert claim row\n  const rows = await (tx as unknown as postgres.Sql)`\n    INSERT INTO referral_claims (...)\n    VALUES (...)\n    RETURNING ...\n  `;\n  \n  // Emit event in same transaction\n  await emitEvent(\n    tx as unknown as postgres.Sql,\n    EventTypes.REFERRAL_CLAIM_REQUESTED,\n    {\n      claimId: row.id,\n      wallet: row.wallet,\n      amountLamports: row.amount_lamports,\n      requestedAt: new Date().toISOString(),\n    },\n  );\n  \n  return row;\n});\n```\n\n### 4. **Worker Processing**\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/queue/worker.ts`\n\nThe worker polls the `event_queue` table and dispatches events. Key behaviors:\n\n**Concurrency Safety**:\n- Uses `FOR UPDATE SKIP LOCKED` to claim batches atomically\n- Multiple workers can safely poll simultaneously (each event processed exactly once)\n\n**Poll Cycle**:\n1. Claim a batch of `pending` events scheduled for now\n2. Move them to `processing` status, record `started_at`\n3. For each event:\n   - Look up the registered handler\n   - Call handler with the payload\n   - On success: mark `completed`, record `completed_at`\n   - On failure: increment `attempts`, apply exponential backoff, reschedule as `pending`\n   - On exhausted retries: mark `dead`, record error message and `completed_at`\n\n**Error Handling**:\n- If no handler is registered: mark event `dead` immediately with alert-level logging (\"MANUAL REVIEW NEEDED\")\n- If handler throws: retry with exponential backoff: attempt 1 → 5s, attempt 2 → 30s, attempt 3+ → 300s\n- Unregistered event types are detected at runtime and logged as dead events\n\n**Status Transitions**:\n```\npending → processing → completed\n       ↓\n       → pending (with scheduled_at + backoff) → processing → completed\n       ↓ (max attempts exhausted)\n       → dead\n```\n\n**Concurrency Model**:\n- `setTimeout(loop, pollIntervalMs)` pattern (same as settlement worker)\n- In-flight poll tracked so `stop()` waits for current batch to finish\n- Default poll interval: 1500ms\n- Default batch size: 10\n\n**Initialization** (from `src/index.ts`):\n```typescript\nconst eventWorker = createEventWorker(sql, {\n  pollIntervalMs: config.eventQueuePollMs,\n});\neventWorker.start();\n```\n\n### 5. **Database Schema**\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/services/backend/migrations/010_event_queue.sql`\n\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE event_queue (\n  id              BIGSERIAL    PRIMARY KEY,\n  event_type      TEXT         NOT NULL,\n  payload         JSONB        NOT NULL,\n  status          TEXT         NOT NULL DEFAULT 'pending',\n  attempts        INTEGER      NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n  max_attempts    INTEGER      NOT NULL DEFAULT 3,\n  scheduled_at    TIMESTAMPTZ  NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),\n  started_at      TIMESTAMPTZ,\n  completed_at    TIMESTAMPTZ,\n  error           TEXT,\n  created_at      TIMESTAMPTZ  NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),\n  \n  CONSTRAINT chk_event_queue_status\n    CHECK (status IN ('pending', 'processing', 'completed', 'failed', 'dead'))\n);\n\n-- Partial index for polling (only pending events)\nCREATE INDEX idx_event_queue_poll\n  ON event_queue (scheduled_at)\n  WHERE status = 'pending';\n\n-- Index for observability\nCREATE INDEX idx_event_queue_status\n  ON event_queue (status, created_at);\n```\n\nPayload is stored as JSONB for flexibility and query-ability.\n\n### 6. **Existing Handlers (None Yet Implemented)**\n\n**Current Status**: No handler implementations exist yet. The infrastructure is ready but all three event types (`REFERRAL_CODE_APPLIED`, `REFERRAL_GAME_SETTLED`, `REFERRAL_CLAIM_REQUESTED`) have no registered handlers.\n\nThis is safe because:\n- Dead events are marked immediately with alert-level logging\n- The event is persisted in the database for manual inspection/replay\n- No silent failures\n\n### 7. **Testing Infrastructure**\n\n**Unit Tests** (`queue.test.ts`):\n- Event insertion with atomic rollback\n- Handler registry get/register\n- Backoff calculation\n\n**Integration Tests** (`queue-integration.test.ts`):\n- Happy path: handler called → event status = completed\n- Failure → retry → dead: attempts incremented, backoff applied\n- Concurrent safety: two workers processing same batch simultaneously, each event exactly once\n\n### 8. **Health/Observability**\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/queue/health.ts`\n\nExports `getQueueDepth()`:\n```typescript\ninterface QueueDepth {\n  pending: number;\n  processing: number;\n  dead: number;\n  completed: number;\n}\n```\n\nQueries the event_queue table grouped by status. Used for monitoring dead events and queue congestion.\n\n---\n\n## Key Patterns Summary\n\n| Aspect | Pattern |\n|--------|---------|\n| **Handler Registration** | Simple `Map<string, handler>` — register once at startup |\n| **Payload Shape** | `Record<string, unknown>` — flexible, schema-less |\n| **Idempotency** | Handlers must be idempotent; no guarantees of single delivery |\n| **Error Handling** | Exponential backoff (5s → 30s → 300s) → dead with error message |\n| **Atomicity** | Events emitted within tx; rolled back if tx fails |\n| **Concurrency** | `FOR UPDATE SKIP LOCKED` on poll; safe for multiple workers |\n| **Scheduling** | `scheduledAt` column enables deferred processing |\n| **Observability** | Dead events logged at WARN level; status/created_at indexed |\n\n---\n\n## File Paths (Absolute)\n\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/queue/event-types.ts` — event type constants\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/queue/handler-registry.ts` — registration/dispatch\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/queue/emit-event.ts` — event producer\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/queue/worker.ts` — polling + dispatch engine\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/queue/health.ts` — queue depth queries\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/queue/index.ts` — public exports\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/migrations/010_event_queue.sql` — schema\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/routes/referral.ts` — example usage (POST /claim)\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/index.ts` — worker initialization"}],"totalDurationMs":104503,"totalTokens":59086,"totalToolUseCount":21,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":538,"cache_read_input_tokens":56067,"output_tokens":2481,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":538},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
