{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SudYo6eB5Lw6yTao4p7t2j","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information needed. Let me create a comprehensive summary report.\n\n## Summary\n\nI've successfully read and analyzed the referral system backend implementation in the RNG Utopia project. Here's the complete picture:\n\n### **Existing Backend Implementation Status**\n\n#### **1. Routes (`/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/routes/referral.ts`)**\n\nThe referral routes file contains 6 fully implemented endpoints:\n- **`POST /referral/code`** - Set/replace player's custom referral code (3-16 chars, `[a-z0-9-]`)\n- **`GET /referral/code`** - Get player's current referral code\n- **`POST /referral/apply`** - Link authenticated player to a referrer via code\n- **`GET /referral/stats`** - Return referral summary (referred count, active count, volume, earned, pending)\n- **`GET /referral/earnings`** - Paginated per-game earnings log\n- **`POST /referral/claim`** - Request async payout of pending balance (202 Accepted response)\n- **`GET /referral/claim/:claimId`** - Poll claim status\n\n**Key Implementation Details:**\n- All endpoints require JWT authentication (validated in middleware)\n- Code validation enforces 3-16 chars, lowercase alphanumeric + hyphens only\n- Self-referral is blocked with clear error codes\n- Code uniqueness enforced at DB level with race condition handling\n- **Claim endpoint emits `REFERRAL_CLAIM_REQUESTED` event** atomically within a DB transaction (lines 345-372)\n  - Uses `sql.begin()` to wrap both the claim insert and event emission\n  - Event payload includes: `claimId`, `wallet`, `amountLamports`, `requestedAt`\n  - Returns 202 with claim ID for polling\n\n#### **2. Database Client (`/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/db.ts`)**\n\nComplete DB interface implementation with these referral-specific methods (lines 313-414):\n\n**Referral Code Methods:**\n- `insertReferralCode(wallet, code)` - Insert new code, throws on duplicate\n- `getReferralCodeByWallet(wallet)` - Look up player's code\n- `getReferralCodeByCode(code)` - Look up code's owner\n- `upsertReferralCode(wallet, code)` - Set or replace code (INSERT...ON CONFLICT UPDATE)\n\n**Referral Link Methods:**\n- `insertReferralLink(referrerWallet, refereeWallet)` - Create binding\n- `getReferralLinkByReferee(refereeWallet)` - Look up a player's referrer\n- `getReferralLinksByReferrer(referrerWallet)` - Get all players referred by a wallet\n\n**Referral Earning Methods:**\n- `insertReferralEarning(params)` - Record earning from a game (with referrer_earned, referee_rebate, rates)\n- `getPendingBalance(wallet)` - **Key method**: Sum of referrer_earned + referee_rebate minus completed claims (lines 862-882)\n  - Returns lamport string (SQL aggregation with COALESCE handling nulls)\n  - Subtracts claims in `pending|processing|completed` states\n- `getReferralEarnings(wallet, page, limit)` - Paginated earnings per referrer\n- `getReferralStats(wallet)` - Summary stats with active count (7d filter) and pending balance\n\n**Referral Claim Methods:**\n- `insertReferralClaim(wallet, amountLamports)` - Create claim with `pending` status (lines 938-945)\n- `getReferralClaim(claimId)` - Fetch claim by UUID (lines 947-952)\n- `updateClaimStatus(claimId, status, meta)` - Update status and metadata (tx_signature, error) (lines 954-966)\n  - Sets `processed_at = now()` when status is `completed` or `failed`\n\n**Utility Methods:**\n- `getReferrerRate(wallet, defaultRateBps)` - Fetch KOL override rate or return default\n- `withTransaction<T>(fn)` - Execute function in transaction (lines 975-978)\n\n#### **3. Configuration (`/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/config.ts`)**\n\nConfig interface and loading (lines 4-104):\n- **`referralDefaultRateBps`** (line 23) - Default referrer share of fee (env: `REFERRAL_DEFAULT_RATE_BPS`, default: 1000 = 10% of total fee)\n- **`referralMinClaimLamports`** (line 24) - Minimum claim amount (env: `REFERRAL_MIN_CLAIM_LAMPORTS`, default: 10000000 = 0.01 SOL)\n\nThese are loaded in `loadConfig()` (lines 95-102):\n```typescript\nreferralDefaultRateBps: parseInt(\n  process.env.REFERRAL_DEFAULT_RATE_BPS ?? \"1000\",\n  10,\n),\nreferralMinClaimLamports: parseInt(\n  process.env.REFERRAL_MIN_CLAIM_LAMPORTS ?? \"10000000\",\n  10,\n),\n```\n\n#### **4. Backend Wiring (`/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/index.ts`)**\n\nRoute registration (lines 93-98):\n```typescript\napp.use(\n  \"/referral/*\",\n  createJwtAuthMiddleware({ jwtSecret: config.jwtSecret, requireAllMethods: true }),\n);\napp.route(\"/referral\", createReferralRoutes({ db, sql, config }));\n```\n\nThe `createReferralRoutes` receives:\n- `db` - database client (all DB methods available)\n- `sql` - raw postgres connection for transactions\n- `config` - config with `referralMinClaimLamports` and `referralDefaultRateBps`\n\n#### **5. Event Queue Infrastructure**\n\n**Event Types** (`/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/queue/event-types.ts`):\n```typescript\nexport const EventTypes = {\n  REFERRAL_CODE_APPLIED: \"referral.code_applied\",\n  REFERRAL_GAME_SETTLED: \"referral.game_settled\",\n  REFERRAL_CLAIM_REQUESTED: \"referral.claim_requested\",\n} as const;\n```\n\n**Event Emission** (`queue/emit-event.ts`):\n- `emitEvent(tx, eventType, payload, options?)` - Inserts event into `event_queue` table atomically within transaction\n- Payload is JSONB-serialized\n- Supports `maxAttempts` and `scheduledAt` options\n\n**Event Processing** (`queue/worker.ts`):\n- Worker polls `event_queue` for `pending` events with `scheduled_at <= now()`\n- Uses `FOR UPDATE SKIP LOCKED` for safe concurrency\n- Dispatches to registered handlers via `getHandler(eventType)`\n- If no handler found → marks `dead` with \"no handler registered\" error\n- On handler success → marks `completed`\n- On handler failure → retries with exponential backoff (5s → 30s → 300s) up to `max_attempts`\n- Exceeded attempts → marks `dead`\n\n**Handler Registry** (`queue/handler-registry.ts`):\n- `registerHandler(eventType, handler)` - Register event handler\n- `getHandler(eventType)` - Look up handler\n- `clearHandlers()` - Clear all (for tests)\n\nHandlers have type: `(payload: Record<string, unknown>) => Promise<void>`\n\n#### **6. Database Schema**\n\n**Referral Tables** (`migrations/011_referral.sql`):\n- `referral_codes` - wallet → code mapping (UNIQUE on both)\n- `referral_links` - referrer → referee immutable binding (UNIQUE on referee_wallet)\n- `referral_earnings` - per-game earning rows with referrer_earned_lamports, referee_rebate_lamports, rates (UNIQUE on referee_wallet + round_id)\n- `referral_claims` - async claim tracking (status: `pending|processing|completed|failed`)\n- `referral_kol_rates` - admin-set KOL overrides\n\n**Event Queue Table** (`migrations/010_event_queue.sql`):\n- `event_queue` - async events with status tracking\n- Columns: id, event_type, payload (JSONB), status, attempts, max_attempts, scheduled_at, started_at, completed_at, error, created_at\n- Partial index on `(scheduled_at)` WHERE status='pending' for efficient polling\n\n---\n\n### **What's Not Yet Implemented (Per Spec)**\n\nAs per the spec checklist (line 627-628), the **ONE critical missing piece** is:\n\n**Claim Queue Handler** - `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/queue/` needs:\n- Handler registered for `REFERRAL_CLAIM_REQUESTED` event type\n- Handler flow:\n  1. Load claim by ID\n  2. Check status is `pending` (idempotency: skip if already `completed`)\n  3. Update to `processing`\n  4. Re-verify available balance >= claim amount (prevents overpay on concurrent claims)\n  5. Execute SOL transfer from server keypair (treasury) to player wallet\n  6. Record `tx_signature`\n  7. Update status to `completed`\n  8. On failure: record error, update to `failed`\n\nThis handler doesn't exist yet. The event is being emitted correctly (in `referral.ts` line 360-369), but no consumer exists to process it.\n\n---\n\n### **File Paths for Reference**\n\n```\n/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/\n├── routes/referral.ts                 ✓ DONE - 6 endpoints + claim event emission\n├── db.ts                              ✓ DONE - all DB methods, getPendingBalance, updateClaimStatus\n├── config.ts                          ✓ DONE - referralDefaultRateBps, referralMinClaimLamports\n├── index.ts                           ✓ DONE - routes wired with JWT + config\n├── queue/\n│   ├── event-types.ts                 ✓ DONE - REFERRAL_CLAIM_REQUESTED defined\n│   ├── emit-event.ts                  ✓ DONE - emitEvent function for atomic emission\n│   ├── handler-registry.ts            ✓ DONE - registerHandler, getHandler API\n│   └── worker.ts                      ✓ DONE - poll/dispatch/retry infrastructure\n├── migrations/\n│   ├── 010_event_queue.sql           ✓ DONE - event_queue table\n│   └── 011_referral.sql              ✓ DONE - all referral tables\n```"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: aeb18c3fbb7dee8d8 (use SendMessage with to: 'aeb18c3fbb7dee8d8' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 88627\ntool_uses: 32\nduration_ms: 199480</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"666b10e8-ff74-42a6-8a85-f241f06f2d89","uuid":"3f20c18a-047f-4186-99c2-269f1f911963","timestamp":"2026-03-25T12:42:04.902Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"In `sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/`, read:\n1. `routes/referral.ts` - the existing referral routes (look at the claim endpoint and how it emits events)\n2. The `db.ts` file - specifically the referral-related methods: `getReferralClaim`, `updateClaimStatus`, `getPendingBalance`, and how the Db interface is typed\n3. The config type (where `referralMinClaimLamports` is defined)\n4. The `index.ts` file to se