{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Uwj6aJcpNBERkrvU3gMqdx","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me compile the comprehensive report:\n\n## Backend SOL Transfer & Transaction Patterns - Complete Analysis\n\n### 1. **settle-tx.ts** - How Server Keypair is Used for On-Chain Transactions\n\n**File Location**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/worker/settle-tx.ts`\n\n#### Key Structure:\n- **Dependencies Interface** (line 58-64):\n  ```typescript\n  export interface SettleTxDeps {\n    db: Db;\n    connection: Connection;\n    serverKeypair: Keypair;\n    entropyAccount: PublicKey;\n    referralDefaultRateBps: number;\n  }\n  ```\n\n#### Transaction Building Pattern (Coinflip Settlement - lines 305-318):\n```typescript\nconst { blockhash, lastValidBlockHeight } = latestBlockhash;\n\nconst tx = new Transaction({\n  feePayer: serverKeypair.publicKey,\n  blockhash,\n  lastValidBlockHeight,\n});\ntx.add(instruction);\ntx.sign(serverKeypair);\n\nconst rawTx = tx.serialize();\nconst txSignature = await connection.sendRawTransaction(rawTx, {\n  skipPreflight: false,\n});\n```\n\n#### Settlement Instruction Building (lines 284-301):\n- Creates `TransactionInstruction` with 8 accounts\n- **Fee payer**: `serverKeypair.publicKey` (signer, writable)\n- **Key accounts**: match PDA, platform config, entropy account, **treasury**, creator, opponent\n- Instruction data: 40 bytes (8-byte discriminator + 32-byte secret)\n- **No direct SOL transfer** - relies on on-chain program to distribute payouts\n\n#### Confirmation Pattern (lines 331-340):\n```typescript\nconst confirmation = await connection.confirmTransaction(\n  { signature: txSignature, blockhash, lastValidBlockHeight },\n  \"confirmed\",\n);\nif (confirmation.value.err) {\n  throw new TransientSettleError(`...`);\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. **index.ts** - Server Keypair Loading & Solana Connection Setup\n\n**File Location**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/index.ts`\n\n#### RPC Connection Initialization (lines 35-38):\n```typescript\nconst connection = new Connection(config.rpcUrl, {\n  commitment: \"confirmed\",\n  ...(config.wsRpcUrl ? { wsEndpoint: config.wsRpcUrl } : {}),\n});\n```\n- Uses **v1 web3.js** (imported line 4: `Connection, PublicKey`)\n- Commitment level: `\"confirmed\"`\n- Optional WebSocket endpoint for real-time subscriptions\n\n#### Settlement Worker Setup (lines 117-125):\n```typescript\nconst entropyAccount = new PublicKey(config.entropyAccount);\nconst retrySettler = createRetrySettler({\n  db,\n  connection,\n  settleRound: (pda) =>\n    settleRound(\n      { db, connection, serverKeypair: config.serverKeypair, \n        entropyAccount, referralDefaultRateBps: config.referralDefaultRateBps },\n      pda,\n    ),\n});\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. **config.ts** - Server Keypair Loading\n\n**File Location**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/config.ts`\n\n#### Keypair Parsing (lines 35-44):\n```typescript\nfunction parseKeypair(raw: string): Keypair {\n  try {\n    const bytes = JSON.parse(raw) as number[];\n    return Keypair.fromSecretKey(Uint8Array.from(bytes));\n  } catch {\n    throw new Error(\n      \"SERVER_KEYPAIR must be a JSON array of secret key bytes (e.g. from solana-keygen)\"\n    );\n  }\n}\n```\n\n#### Config Interface (lines 4-25):\n```typescript\nexport interface Config {\n  port: number;\n  databaseUrl: string;\n  dbSchema: string;\n  rpcUrl: string;\n  wsRpcUrl: string | undefined;\n  serverKeypair: Keypair;\n  jwtSecret: Uint8Array;\n  cluster: string;\n  challengeTtlSeconds: number;\n  accessTokenTtlSeconds: number;\n  refreshTokenTtlDays: number;\n  rateLimitPerWallet: number;\n  rateLimitGlobal: number;\n  workerPollIntervalMs: number;\n  entropyAccount: string;\n  pythBtcUsdAccount: string;\n  minSolBalance: number;\n  eventQueuePollMs: number;\n  referralDefaultRateBps: number;\n  referralMinClaimLamports: number;\n}\n```\n\n#### Environment Loading (line 55):\n```typescript\nserverKeypair: parseKeypair(requireEnv(\"SERVER_KEYPAIR\")),\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Treasury Transfer Patterns**\n\n#### No Direct Transfer - All Through On-Chain Settlement\n\n**Important**: The backend **does NOT perform direct SOL transfers** using `SystemProgram.transfer()`. Instead:\n\n1. **Fee Routing** (lines 265-271 of settle-tx.ts):\n   ```typescript\n   const { feeBps, treasury } = platformConfig;\n   const pool = entryAmount * 2n;\n   const feeAmount = Number((pool * BigInt(feeBps)) / 10_000n);\n   const payoutAmount = Number(pool) - feeAmount;\n   ```\n\n2. **Treasury Account Passed to On-Chain Program** (lines 290 of settle-tx.ts):\n   ```typescript\n   { pubkey: treasury, isSigner: false, isWritable: true }, // treasury\n   ```\n\n3. **Platform Config Provides Treasury Address** (`platform-config.ts` lines 34-50):\n   ```typescript\n   export async function fetchPlatformConfig(\n     connection: Connection,\n   ): Promise<{ feeBps: number; treasury: PublicKey }> {\n     const [pda] = derivePlatformConfigPda();\n     const info = await connection.getAccountInfo(pda);\n     // ...\n     const treasury = new PublicKey(data.subarray(40, 72)); // bytes 40-72\n     const feeBps = data.readUInt16LE(72);\n     return { feeBps, treasury };\n   }\n   ```\n\n**The on-chain Anchor program's `settle` instruction handles payout distribution directly.**\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Web3.js Version & Imports**\n\n**Version**: `@solana/web3.js` v1.98.0 (from backend package.json)\n\n#### Standard v1 Imports Used Throughout:\n```typescript\nimport {\n  Connection,\n  Keypair,\n  PublicKey,\n  SystemProgram,\n  Transaction,\n  TransactionInstruction,\n} from \"@solana/web3.js\";\n```\n\n#### Key v1 Patterns:\n- **Connection**: Single RPC endpoint with commitment level\n- **Transaction**: Legacy transaction format (lines 305-310)\n  ```typescript\n  const tx = new Transaction({\n    feePayer: serverKeypair.publicKey,\n    blockhash,\n    lastValidBlockHeight,\n  });\n  ```\n- **Signing**: `tx.sign(serverKeypair)` (full sign) or `tx.partialSign(serverKeypair)` (co-signing)\n- **Serialization**: `tx.serialize()` or `tx.serialize({ requireAllSignatures: false })`\n- **Transmission**: `connection.sendRawTransaction(rawTx, { skipPreflight: false })`\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Utility for Creating & Sending Transactions**\n\n#### Close Call Transaction Sender (closecall-clock.ts lines 114-149):\n```typescript\nasync function sendAndConfirm(\n  tx: Transaction,\n  label: string,\n): Promise<string> {\n  let lastError: unknown;\n\n  for (let attempt = 0; attempt < MAX_TX_RETRIES; attempt++) {\n    try {\n      const sig = await connection.sendRawTransaction(tx.serialize(), {\n        skipPreflight: false,\n      });\n      const { blockhash, lastValidBlockHeight } =\n        await connection.getLatestBlockhash();\n      const confirmation = await connection.confirmTransaction(\n        { signature: sig, blockhash, lastValidBlockHeight },\n        \"confirmed\",\n      );\n      if (confirmation.value.err) {\n        throw new Error(`${label} tx ${sig} confirmed with error: ...`);\n      }\n      return sig;\n    } catch (err) {\n      lastError = err;\n      if (attempt < MAX_TX_RETRIES - 1) {\n        logger.warn(`closecall clock: ${label} tx attempt ${attempt + 1} failed, retrying`, {...});\n        await new Promise((r) => setTimeout(r, TX_RETRY_DELAY_MS));\n      }\n    }\n  }\n  throw lastError;\n}\n```\n\n#### Close Call Settle Transaction Builder (closecall-clock.ts lines 413-423):\n```typescript\nconst { blockhash, lastValidBlockHeight } =\n  await connection.getLatestBlockhash();\nconst tx = new Transaction({\n  feePayer: serverKeypair.publicKey,\n  blockhash,\n  lastValidBlockHeight,\n});\ntx.add(ix);\ntx.sign(serverKeypair);\n\nconst sig = await sendAndConfirm(tx, \"settle\");\n```\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Transaction Instruction Building Pattern** (for reference)\n\n#### Instruction Structure Example - Coinflip Settle (lines 284-301):\n```typescript\nconst instruction = new TransactionInstruction({\n  keys: [\n    { pubkey: serverKeypair.publicKey, isSigner: true, isWritable: true }, // caller\n    { pubkey: matchPubkey, isSigner: false, isWritable: true }, // coinflip_match\n    { pubkey: platformConfigPda, isSigner: false, isWritable: false }, // platform_config\n    { pubkey: entropyAccount, isSigner: false, isWritable: false }, // slot_hashes sysvar\n    { pubkey: treasury, isSigner: false, isWritable: true }, // treasury\n    { pubkey: creator, isSigner: false, isWritable: true }, // creator\n    { pubkey: opponent, isSigner: false, isWritable: true }, // opponent\n    { pubkey: SystemProgram.programId, isSigner: false, isWritable: false }, // system_program\n  ],\n  programId: COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID,\n  data,\n});\n```\n\n**Note**: `SystemProgram.programId` is passed as an account, not for creating transfer instructions.\n\n---\n\n### Summary\n\nThe backend uses a **clean separation of concerns**:\n\n1. **Backend calculates fees and payouts** but doesn't send SOL\n2. **Treasury address is read from on-chain PlatformConfig** (admin-updatable)\n3. **All payouts are disbursed by the on-chain Anchor program** when the settle instruction executes\n4. **Server keypair is solely the fee payer** for submit transactions\n5. **No direct `SystemProgram.transfer()` calls** exist in the backend code\n6. Uses **web3.js v1** exclusively with standard legacy Transaction format"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a8eabb4957420796a (use SendMessage with to: 'a8eabb4957420796a' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 73020\ntool_uses: 20\nduration_ms: 134724</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"666b10e8-ff74-42a6-8a85-f241f06f2d89","uuid":"ded12c02-7d4f-4ebb-aea0-a720e4d708ab","timestamp":"2026-03-25T12:44:32.143Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"In `sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/`, I need to understand how the backend performs SOL transfers / on-chain transactions. Specifically:\n\n1. Read `settle-tx.ts` - how does it use the server keypair? Is there an RPC connection used for sending transactions?\n2. Read `index.ts` - how is the server keypair loaded? How is the Solana connection set up?\n3. Look for any existing treasury transfer patterns (how SOL is sent from the server wallet to a player wallet)\n4. Check what `@solana/web3.js` imports are used - is it v1 (Connection, Keypair, SystemProgram, Transaction) or v2?\n5. Check if there's a utility for creating and sending simple SOL transfer transactions\n\nReport the exact patterns, imports, and function signatures used.","agentId":"a8eabb4957420796a","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me compile the comprehensive report:\n\n## Backend SOL Transfer & Transaction Patterns - Complete Analysis\n\n### 1. **settle-tx.ts** - How Server Keypair is Used for On-Chain Transactions\n\n**File Location**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/worker/settle-tx.ts`\n\n#### Key Structure:\n- **Dependencies Interface** (line 58-64):\n  ```typescript\n  export interface SettleTxDeps {\n    db: Db;\n    connection: Connection;\n    serverKeypair: Keypair;\n    entropyAccount: PublicKey;\n    referralDefaultRateBps: number;\n  }\n  ```\n\n#### Transaction Building Pattern (Coinflip Settlement - lines 305-318):\n```typescript\nconst { blockhash, lastValidBlockHeight } = latestBlockhash;\n\nconst tx = new Transaction({\n  feePayer: serverKeypair.publicKey,\n  blockhash,\n  lastValidBlockHeight,\n});\ntx.add(instruction);\ntx.sign(serverKeypair);\n\nconst rawTx = tx.serialize();\nconst txSignature = await connection.sendRawTransaction(rawTx, {\n  skipPreflight: false,\n});\n```\n\n#### Settlement Instruction Building (lines 284-301):\n- Creates `TransactionInstruction` with 8 accounts\n- **Fee payer**: `serverKeypair.publicKey` (signer, writable)\n- **Key accounts**: match PDA, platform config, entropy account, **treasury**, creator, opponent\n- Instruction data: 40 bytes (8-byte discriminator + 32-byte secret)\n- **No direct SOL transfer** - relies on on-chain program to distribute payouts\n\n#### Confirmation Pattern (lines 331-340):\n```typescript\nconst confirmation = await connection.confirmTransaction(\n  { signature: txSignature, blockhash, lastValidBlockHeight },\n  \"confirmed\",\n);\nif (confirmation.value.err) {\n  throw new TransientSettleError(`...`);\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. **index.ts** - Server Keypair Loading & Solana Connection Setup\n\n**File Location**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/index.ts`\n\n#### RPC Connection Initialization (lines 35-38):\n```typescript\nconst connection = new Connection(config.rpcUrl, {\n  commitment: \"confirmed\",\n  ...(config.wsRpcUrl ? { wsEndpoint: config.wsRpcUrl } : {}),\n});\n```\n- Uses **v1 web3.js** (imported line 4: `Connection, PublicKey`)\n- Commitment level: `\"confirmed\"`\n- Optional WebSocket endpoint for real-time subscriptions\n\n#### Settlement Worker Setup (lines 117-125):\n```typescript\nconst entropyAccount = new PublicKey(config.entropyAccount);\nconst retrySettler = createRetrySettler({\n  db,\n  connection,\n  settleRound: (pda) =>\n    settleRound(\n      { db, connection, serverKeypair: config.serverKeypair, \n        entropyAccount, referralDefaultRateBps: config.referralDefaultRateBps },\n      pda,\n    ),\n});\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. **config.ts** - Server Keypair Loading\n\n**File Location**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/config.ts`\n\n#### Keypair Parsing (lines 35-44):\n```typescript\nfunction parseKeypair(raw: string): Keypair {\n  try {\n    const bytes = JSON.parse(raw) as number[];\n    return Keypair.fromSecretKey(Uint8Array.from(bytes));\n  } catch {\n    throw new Error(\n      \"SERVER_KEYPAIR must be a JSON array of secret key bytes (e.g. from solana-keygen)\"\n    );\n  }\n}\n```\n\n#### Config Interface (lines 4-25):\n```typescript\nexport interface Config {\n  port: number;\n  databaseUrl: string;\n  dbSchema: string;\n  rpcUrl: string;\n  wsRpcUrl: string | undefined;\n  serverKeypair: Keypair;\n  jwtSecret: Uint8Array;\n  cluster: string;\n  challengeTtlSeconds: number;\n  accessTokenTtlSeconds: number;\n  refreshTokenTtlDays: number;\n  rateLimitPerWallet: number;\n  rateLimitGlobal: number;\n  workerPollIntervalMs: number;\n  entropyAccount: string;\n  pythBtcUsdAccount: string;\n  minSolBalance: number;\n  eventQueuePollMs: number;\n  referralDefaultRateBps: number;\n  referralMinClaimLamports: number;\n}\n```\n\n#### Environment Loading (line 55):\n```typescript\nserverKeypair: parseKeypair(requireEnv(\"SERVER_KEYPAIR\")),\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Treasury Transfer Patterns**\n\n#### No Direct Transfer - All Through On-Chain Settlement\n\n**Important**: The backend **does NOT perform direct SOL transfers** using `SystemProgram.transfer()`. Instead:\n\n1. **Fee Routing** (lines 265-271 of settle-tx.ts):\n   ```typescript\n   const { feeBps, treasury } = platformConfig;\n   const pool = entryAmount * 2n;\n   const feeAmount = Number((pool * BigInt(feeBps)) / 10_000n);\n   const payoutAmount = Number(pool) - feeAmount;\n   ```\n\n2. **Treasury Account Passed to On-Chain Program** (lines 290 of settle-tx.ts):\n   ```typescript\n   { pubkey: treasury, isSigner: false, isWritable: true }, // treasury\n   ```\n\n3. **Platform Config Provides Treasury Address** (`platform-config.ts` lines 34-50):\n   ```typescript\n   export async function fetchPlatformConfig(\n     connection: Connection,\n   ): Promise<{ feeBps: number; treasury: PublicKey }> {\n     const [pda] = derivePlatformConfigPda();\n     const info = await connection.getAccountInfo(pda);\n     // ...\n     const treasury = new PublicKey(data.subarray(40, 72)); // bytes 40-72\n     const feeBps = data.readUInt16LE(72);\n     return { feeBps, treasury };\n   }\n   ```\n\n**The on-chain Anchor program's `settle` instruction handles payout distribution directly.**\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Web3.js Version & Imports**\n\n**Version**: `@solana/web3.js` v1.98.0 (from backend package.json)\n\n#### Standard v1 Imports Used Throughout:\n```typescript\nimport {\n  Connection,\n  Keypair,\n  PublicKey,\n  SystemProgram,\n  Transaction,\n  TransactionInstruction,\n} from \"@solana/web3.js\";\n```\n\n#### Key v1 Patterns:\n- **Connection**: Single RPC endpoint with commitment level\n- **Transaction**: Legacy transaction format (lines 305-310)\n  ```typescript\n  const tx = new Transaction({\n    feePayer: serverKeypair.publicKey,\n    blockhash,\n    lastValidBlockHeight,\n  });\n  ```\n- **Signing**: `tx.sign(serverKeypair)` (full sign) or `tx.partialSign(serverKeypair)` (co-signing)\n- **Serialization**: `tx.serialize()` or `tx.serialize({ requireAllSignatures: false })`\n- **Transmission**: `connection.sendRawTransaction(rawTx, { skipPreflight: false })`\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Utility for Creating & Sending Transactions**\n\n#### Close Call Transaction Sender (closecall-clock.ts lines 114-149):\n```typescript\nasync function sendAndConfirm(\n  tx: Transaction,\n  label: string,\n): Promise<string> {\n  let lastError: unknown;\n\n  for (let attempt = 0; attempt < MAX_TX_RETRIES; attempt++) {\n    try {\n      const sig = await connection.sendRawTransaction(tx.serialize(), {\n        skipPreflight: false,\n      });\n      const { blockhash, lastValidBlockHeight } =\n        await connection.getLatestBlockhash();\n      const confirmation = await connection.confirmTransaction(\n        { signature: sig, blockhash, lastValidBlockHeight },\n        \"confirmed\",\n      );\n      if (confirmation.value.err) {\n        throw new Error(`${label} tx ${sig} confirmed with error: ...`);\n      }\n      return sig;\n    } catch (err) {\n      lastError = err;\n      if (attempt < MAX_TX_RETRIES - 1) {\n        logger.warn(`closecall clock: ${label} tx attempt ${attempt + 1} failed, retrying`, {...});\n        await new Promise((r) => setTimeout(r, TX_RETRY_DELAY_MS));\n      }\n    }\n  }\n  throw lastError;\n}\n```\n\n#### Close Call Settle Transaction Builder (closecall-clock.ts lines 413-423):\n```typescript\nconst { blockhash, lastValidBlockHeight } =\n  await connection.getLatestBlockhash();\nconst tx = new Transaction({\n  feePayer: serverKeypair.publicKey,\n  blockhash,\n  lastValidBlockHeight,\n});\ntx.add(ix);\ntx.sign(serverKeypair);\n\nconst sig = await sendAndConfirm(tx, \"settle\");\n```\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Transaction Instruction Building Pattern** (for reference)\n\n#### Instruction Structure Example - Coinflip Settle (lines 284-301):\n```typescript\nconst instruction = new TransactionInstruction({\n  keys: [\n    { pubkey: serverKeypair.publicKey, isSigner: true, isWritable: true }, // caller\n    { pubkey: matchPubkey, isSigner: false, isWritable: true }, // coinflip_match\n    { pubkey: platformConfigPda, isSigner: false, isWritable: false }, // platform_config\n    { pubkey: entropyAccount, isSigner: false, isWritable: false }, // slot_hashes sysvar\n    { pubkey: treasury, isSigner: false, isWritable: true }, // treasury\n    { pubkey: creator, isSigner: false, isWritable: true }, // creator\n    { pubkey: opponent, isSigner: false, isWritable: true }, // opponent\n    { pubkey: SystemProgram.programId, isSigner: false, isWritable: false }, // system_program\n  ],\n  programId: COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID,\n  data,\n});\n```\n\n**Note**: `SystemProgram.programId` is passed as an account, not for creating transfer instructions.\n\n---\n\n### Summary\n\nThe backend uses a **clean separation of concerns**:\n\n1. **Backend calculates fees and payouts** but doesn't send SOL\n2. **Treasury address is read from on-chain PlatformConfig** (admin-updatable)\n3. **All payouts are disbursed by the on-chain Anchor program** when the settle instruction executes\n4. **Server keypair is solely the fee payer** for submit transactions\n5. **No direct `SystemProgram.transfer()` calls** exist in the backend code\n6. Uses **web3.js v1** exclusively with standard legacy Transaction format"}],"totalDurationMs":134724,"totalTokens":73020,"totalToolUseCount":20,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3457,"cache_read_input_tokens":66734,"output_tokens":2827,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":3457},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
